        <p class="metadata">Posted by Matthew Weier O'Phinney (matthew) on 2007-02-14T14:30:22.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>This can be done very easily for all Zend_Service_Abstract-based components:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$httpClient = new Zend_Http_Client(null, array( 
    'adapter'    =&gt; 'Zend_Http_Client_Adapter_Proxy', 
    'proxy_host' =&gt; 'proxy.example.com', 
    'proxy_port' =&gt; 8080, 
    'proxy_user' =&gt; 'me', 
    'proxy_pass' =&gt; 'bananarama' 
)); 
 
// Pass it into the akismet client 
Zend_Service_Akismet::setHttpClient($httpClient);
</code></pre>

<p>The service classes themselves do not need to implement the behaviour.</p>

